<dl id="n36005f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36005f">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36005f"> 5(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Niponbashy</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The bridges over the Sumida, and those which span the canals, have always been distinctive features of Tokyo. The <mark>Nihon-bashi</mark> (Bridge of Japan), in the district of the same name, is by far the most famous. It is the point from which all distances in Japan are measured. <small> &ldquo;TOKYO&rdquo; <a name="EBTK" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBTK"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 1048a</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
